Boil a #pot{} of @water{350%ml} with a pinch of @salt{} and preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{1}(roughly chopped) and the @coriander{½}(roughly chopped). Cut the @aubergine{1} in half lengthways, then each half into four strips. Chop widthways into 3cm chunks. Remove the ends off the @green beans{½}(ends removed and chopped into thirds).

Add the @basmati rice{175%g} to your pot of boiling water. Cover with a tight lid and place on the lowest heat for ~{10%minutes}. Take the pot off the heat to rest for ~{10%minutes}.

> Do not lift the lid from the pot at all during cooking and resting.

Coat your aubergine evenly in a splash of @olive oil{}. Sprinkle over a pinch of @salt{} and a generous amount of @black pepper{}. Pop onto a #baking tray{} lined with baking paper and cook on the top shelf of your oven for ~{20%minutes} or until slightly crispy.

Heat a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Without adding any oil, put the @cashew nuts{25%g} in the pan for around ~{5%minutes}, shaking the pan constantly, until your cashew nuts are brown, then remove to one side.

> Watch your nuts like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Add a splash of @oil{} to the now empty #frying pan{} together with the @massaman curry paste{1}. Stir your paste for ~{1%minute} and then add the @coconut milk{200%ml} and mushrooms. Once your coconut milk comes to the boil, add your beans and @peanut butter{1.5%tbsp} and turn the heat to low. Simmer gently for ~{10%minutes}.

Add your roasted aubergine to your curry mixture.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and add it to the pan with your curry mixture. Gently fold in your cooked rice and three-quarters of your coriander. Squeeze over some @lime{½}(juiced) and stir in. Serve into bowls and garnish with your remaining coriander and cashew nuts.